# Bookmgr - Book Management System

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Go 1.26+ | Chi v5 | Ent ORM | uber-go/fx | golang-jwt/jwt v5
- Frontend: React 19 | TypeScript | Vite | React Router
- Database: PostgreSQL 16 | Deployment: Docker Compose

## Architecture
- NO internal/ directory in backend
- Layers: handler/ -> service/ -> repository/ -> ent/ -> PostgreSQL
- All DI via uber-go/fx (each package exports a Module variable)
- Frontend: single React app, routes split /admin/* and /console/*
- JWT auth: middleware validates Bearer token, claims {sub, role, exp}

## Conventions
- Go: gofmt, error wrapping with fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err), no global state
- TypeScript: strict mode, functional components, hooks only
- API: /api/v1/ prefix, JSON bodies, standard error format {"error","code"}
- Ent schemas in backend/ent/schema/, generated code committed
- Run `go generate ./ent` after schema changes

## Key Paths
- Entry point: backend/cmd/server/main.go
- Ent schemas: backend/ent/schema/
- Handlers: backend/handler/
- Services: backend/service/
- Frontend pages: frontend/src/pages/admin/, frontend/src/pages/console/

## Key Commands
- Backend: `cd backend && go run ./cmd/server`
- Frontend: `cd frontend && npm run dev`
- Docker: `docker compose up -d`
- Ent codegen: `cd backend && go generate ./ent`
